# 1000G-CNV-Reference-Builder

Automated workflow for constructing a **high-quality whole genome sequencing (WGS) reference cohort** from the **1000 Genomes Project high-coverage (30×) GRCh38 dataset** for **copy number variation (CNV) baseline generation**.

This project was developed to create a robust **Panel of Normals (PoN)** suitable for **CNVkit** and other read-depth–based CNV callers by downloading, filtering, and quality-controlling unrelated high-coverage genomes.

---

## Overview

Read-depth–based CNV callers such as **CNVkit** rely heavily on a high-quality reference baseline to normalize sequencing noise and improve CNV detection accuracy.

This repository automates:

- Selection of **unrelated founder samples**
- Download of **30× WGS CRAM files**
- Resume-safe downloading from **1000 Genomes high coverage release**
- Batch-based downloads for scalability
- Coverage quality control (QC)
- Preparation for downstream **CNV reference generation**

---

## Why This Exists

The original **1000 Genomes Phase 3 release** contains mostly **low-coverage (~4×) genomes**, which are not ideal for read-depth–based CNV reference construction.

This workflow instead uses the:

> **1000 Genomes 2504 high-coverage (~30×) GRCh38 release**

to improve:

- Coverage consistency
- CNV signal stability
- Noise reduction
- Reference normalization quality

for downstream CNV analysis.

---

## Dataset Used

### Source
**1000 Genomes Project – High Coverage Release (2504 samples)**

- Genome build: **GRCh38**
- Sequencing depth: **~30× WGS**
- Platform: **Illumina NovaSeq 6000**
- Alignment format: **CRAM**

### Selection Criteria

Samples are filtered to include:

- **Founder/unrelated individuals**
- **High-coverage (~30×) genomes**
- **GRCh38-aligned WGS**
- Consistent sequencing characteristics

Related samples are excluded to reduce inherited CNV enrichment within the reference cohort.

